LINE.Text: Data is being created every minute of every day without us even noticing it Given how much
information is floating around these days, it's tempting to talk about big data only in terms of
size. Big data describes the massive avalanche of digital activity pulsating through cables and
airwaves, but it also describes all the things we were never able to measure before. With
every status we share, every article we read or every photo we upload, we are creating a
How Much Data is Generated Every Minute?
digital trail that tells a story. Below, we explore how much data is generated in one minute.
